We have come to the general assembly in the church of the firstborn whose names are in heaven.

01:39:12.210 --> 01:39:19.499
We have come to Jesus the mediator of the new covenant and to the blood of sprinkling that speaks of better things than that of Abel.

01:39:19.500 --> 01:39:44.399
Come on, let's lift our hands. Glorify the Lord. I can hear your voice.

01:39:44.400 --> 01:40:12.659
I can touch your face. There is a place of mercy in the mountain of the Lord.

01:40:12.660 --> 01:40:29.950
Your presence, there is a place for those who are lonely. Sing it again.

01:40:29.951 --> 01:40:41.778
I can hear your voice. I'm alone. I can hear the mountain of the Lord.

01:40:41.779 --> 01:40:57.599
I can touch your face. There is a place for those who are in the mountain of the Lord.

01:40:57.600 --> 01:41:49.839
I can feel the mountain of your blessing. There is a place. I said there is a place in the cleft of the Lord.

01:41:49.840 --> 01:41:58.031
I just love his ministry of all the people that... whenever he knew how to hit those...

01:41:58.032 --> 01:42:20.953
when he started to worship and you could feel the vein every single time I listen to him, I just go, 'My goodness.'I try to, you know, whenever there's nights like this, to lead by example, an example of teaching you how.

01:42:20.954 --> 01:42:33.617
It's just awkward because if it was private, I know it's a lot easier for me to do that whenever I know the certain things that I would sing that are private to me.

01:42:33.618 --> 01:42:41.430
But bringing it to you because there's so many of you that think it's just something you just...

01:42:41.431 --> 01:42:49.999
the critics don't get it because they're never going to walk in it anyway. 99% of them will never walk in that place.

01:42:50.000 --> 01:43:01.279
But there are some of you that are so desperate that you want it so bad that you really truly want a relationship with the Lord. Not what Brandon has, but just your own thing.

01:43:01.280 --> 01:43:14.495
And I'm trying to teach you by example, by what I do by finding the books, finding things, and you grasp on to it, and this is how you pull yourself out of even this dry season.

01:43:14.496 --> 01:43:21.678
I haven't been dry all day. It just was weird. This is weird what happened.

01:43:21.679 --> 01:43:46.104
But getting in that place of that refreshing of where you cultivate his presence, out of your belly shall flow rivers of living waters and you bring yourself up by your bootstraps and not be moved by what you see or what you feel, by just being authentic and real, Father.

01:43:46.105 --> 01:44:04.959
And most people will quit and they don't let it go because they have seasons of dryness and they think, 'Well, if this is what it is, I get tired.'You're always looking at your watch: 'How long have I been in prayer today?

01:44:04.960 --> 01:44:24.169
How long have I been doing this? Is he really there?'And regardless of what I feel right now, even with all you sitting here in my living room, I'm not moved by what I see or what I feel.

01:44:24.170 --> 01:44:33.678
That's where you pull yourself out of that. Faith is not a feeling. Faith is an act.

01:44:33.679 --> 01:44:38.818
Faith doesn't have to be the glory and you seeing things and the holy angel choir and all that you feel.

01:44:38.819 --> 01:44:44.925
Faith is an act. I refuse to be moved by my flesh. I move by what the spirit is.

01:44:44.926 --> 01:44:53.344
And he said he inhabits the praises of his people. And he's always there.

01:44:53.345 --> 01:44:58.447
He's never left me. He's never forsaken me. Lo, unto the end of the earth, he said he'd be with us always.

01:44:58.448 --> 01:45:10.559
And either you have a mindset of that and you realize it, or you don't. It's not a feeling. Prayer comes out of...

01:45:10.560 --> 01:45:21.919
sometimes I hear a lady say to me, 'Brandon, I don't see anything when I pray; I just pray.'Who said you were ever going to?

01:45:21.920 --> 01:45:35.198
Blessed are those that have not seen, yet still believe. And so you just keep pushing on. Does that make sense what I'm saying, son?

01:45:35.199 --> 01:45:49.641
Because I try to make it where it's not so—where there's so many people always trying to parrot it, where you find your own.

01:45:49.642 --> 01:46:02.079
But even when you see—this is a struggle versus just authentic, like it was last time when I felt like the glory of the Lord showed up in the whole house and I could feel it was tangible.

01:46:02.080 --> 01:46:13.975
You know, does that make sense? Yes. I try to make sense instead, because when I'm talking and leading these people, how you push through it.

01:46:13.976 --> 01:46:24.879
So then you go back in; I start worshiping and you sit there, and that's why I say sometimes I sit there for five hours and nothing.

01:46:24.880 --> 01:46:29.710
You feel like you've been there for five hours, and I'll be sitting at my dryer.

01:46:29.711 --> 01:46:38.799
Usually I sit by my dryer because I'm doing laundry, helping Diana with laundry, and I sit there for an hour, five hours, nothing.

01:46:38.800 --> 01:46:45.759
It's like—and then finally you'll hit it and you'll push over and you'll start to see.

01:46:45.760 --> 01:46:53.002
And sometimes it'll be all day long, nothing. And you'll go, 'What?'And I'm just praying.

01:46:53.003 --> 01:47:01.599
You just, 'Father, I just worship you.'And you're going, 'Are you ever going to show up?'I'm looking for that tug on the tugboat.

01:47:01.600 --> 01:47:11.011
Help push me out of this. Help me. Let's do this together. Sometimes it's just instantaneously you just step right over in it.

01:47:11.012 --> 01:47:19.687
But I have always learned: it's always different. And sometimes the more you cultivate, it's easier.

01:47:19.688 --> 01:47:26.762
But even when I asked him today—I knew what he was saying, but I didn't realize it was going to be like this to this degree.

01:47:26.763 --> 01:47:35.118
But when I was in there and I told him, he goes, 'I want you to show them by example, humble yourself.

01:47:35.119 --> 01:47:48.323
Show them it's not always like that.'I said, 'Okay, I get it.'So hopefully it helps you.

01:47:48.324 --> 01:47:55.292
I don't know if it does or not, but if it doesn't, then you say, 'Well, Brandon, this was a waste of time.'You just click out and go on.

01:47:55.293 --> 01:48:06.158
But at least I can say I tried to teach you all as much as I can, and hopefully you're getting something out of it.

01:48:06.159 --> 01:48:13.625
Find—that's when you find the scriptures that pertain to what you're believing for. You go through it.

01:48:13.626 --> 01:48:35.117
And lately, I've been reading Jeremiah over and over and over, and how he went through things where it seemed like he was all alone, where it seemed like he was talking to people and they wanted to kill him for it.

01:48:35.118 --> 01:48:41.794
They didn't like what he was saying. And the other false prophets were telling everybody everything was going to be great.

01:48:41.795 --> 01:48:49.675
And here he was telling everybody that it's going to be judgment and all these other things coming.

01:48:49.676 --> 01:48:57.776
And they're all telling, 'Oh, he's a false prophet.'And he was the only one—he was the voice crying in the wilderness—the only one saying what God told him to really say.

01:48:57.778 --> 01:49:05.542
And they were ready to kill him for it. The kings hated him. And so, going over...

01:49:05.543 --> 01:49:12.879
the Lord said, 'Read it again. Read it again. Go over things.'Faith cometh by hearing, and hearing by the word of God.

01:49:12.880 --> 01:49:20.319
And so I know reading Hebrews and going over that, stirring yourself up.

01:49:20.320 --> 01:49:33.275
But not only that, but leading your family and finding a good church to go to, you pick yourself up.

01:49:33.276 --> 01:49:44.250
You find your supplements of the word during the week and that's how you keep having a foundation of the word of God in your life because that's what's going to keep you strong, the meat of the word.

01:49:44.251 --> 01:49:50.978
And then you bring in the drinking of the word of the Holy Spirit, is what I want to say.

01:49:50.979 --> 01:49:59.039
And that's what hydrates you, and that's what you keep doing.

01:49:59.040 --> 01:50:07.919
So in all that, I think that's just being real instead of trying to be fake.

01:50:07.920 --> 01:50:21.626
So I guess we can end it. I've already taken an hour and 45 minutes of your time. I'm sorry. I don't control it. It is what it is.

01:50:21.627 --> 01:50:26.429
When he wants to show us stuff and he wants to fill it and the vein's there, then you go with it.

01:50:26.430 --> 01:50:40.158
Not you say, 'Well, I do it so much better than you.'Then you sit in front of 7,000 people and you tell them, 'I'll watch you; I'd like to learn.'I don't say I have it all down, right?

01:50:40.159 --> 01:50:46.620
But it is what it is. I'll close it with that so that you all can go do what you want to do.

01:50:46.621 --> 01:50:54.718
But we love you and we thank you for being here tonight and we're so grateful for every single one of you, especially putting up with that.

01:50:54.719 --> 01:51:00.319
Hopefully it blessed you anyway. I don't know what to say other than that.

01:51:00.320 --> 01:51:07.340
But we love you. Remember, put a smile on your face and a song in your heart. Jesus loves you and we love you.

01:51:07.341 --> 01:51:15.748
And we'll see you again probably tomorrow, because I'll dig out of this and we'll get to the other place where we're supposed to be tomorrow.

01:51:15.749 --> 01:51:26.679
I'll come back in the morning or whatever and see. But we'll see you then. God bless you all. Good night.

